name: White-lined Antbird
rangeDescription: Far southwestern amazonian brazil to southeastern peru and northwestern bolivia
description: Large antbird of bamboo stands in river edge forest. Males are dark gray with bright white wing bars and a darker blackish crest that is raised when agitated; females appear two-toned: orange above, with creamy white face and underparts.

name: Chin Hills Wren-Babbler
description: Tiny brown bird with a proportionally long tail and a white breast. The white breast is flecked with dark spots, while the brown upperparts appear scaled.

name: Sao Tome Oriole
rangeDescription: Forest of são tomé (gulf of guinea)
description: Old World oriole that is unusual in nearly lacking yellow in its plumage. There is a dark hood which is solid in males and streaky in females.

name: Golden-eared Tanager
rangeDescription: Andes of southwestern colombia to northwestern bolivia
description: Colorful cloud forest tanager found mainly along the east slope of the Andes. It is bluish-green with an orange face, coppery belly, and bold black markings on the head and back.

name: Peruvian Thick-knee
rangeDescription: Arid littoral of southwestern ecuador to southern peru; one record from northern chile
description: Distinctive, large nocturnal “shorebird” of dry desert habitats in lowlands. Note the big pale eyes, striped head, and long pale yellowish legs.
